<Date>Tue Jul 03 00:00:00 CST 2007
<Content>I bought the gray iPod Shuffle a few months ago, and enjoyed every part of it until someone stole it last week.  Excellent sound, very easy operation, and durability. Nice price for the capacity and design.   For doing things like working out, going to work, or travelling to a near city, you can't go wrong. For many many people who buy bigger ipods, this is actually what they need, not a bigger device. I've had nanos and videos, but it wasn't until I got the new shuffle that I really listened to my favorite music constantly. Think about it, deep inside what your iEars may be really expecting is to hear your REAL favorite tunes all the time... and that's the equivalent of like.. 150, 200, 250 songs?? For most of normal consumers, this is enough. Now if you really really want to have with you all the time your ENTIRE collection, and you really NEED it, then you should look for the more gigas.   The only con? mmmm.. maybe for it being so small, it got stolen! No, seriously, it's a great little thing. For PC people, iTunes-only compatibility may be a stress factor, for me it was ok.   I don't regret having buying it, and definitely would get it again.  
