<Review ID>4478126
<Product Name>Apple iPod shuffle 1 GB Bright Blue (2nd Generation)
<Title>The Almost-Perfect MP3 Player
<Date>Fri Apr 06 00:00:00 CST 2007
<Content>Wow. You probably know all about the Ipod Shuffle already. This review is based on my experience with it - this may not be typical to all users, however I believe that many of these points are valid for all Ipod Shuffle of the 2nd Generation.  The one I am reviewing is the 1GB Ipod Shuffle.  1) Volume : I find the volume to be very uneven. I went to Itunes and increased the volume on all tracks and then transferred the music back to the Ipod, but the volume levels were the same. That said, it sounds just fine even in crowded rooms or airplanes, so this is not really a complaint.  2) Capacity : The ad says it can 240 songs, yet mine could only hold around 180 tracks (note that most of my tracks were pretty low kbps - around 128, most of the time). I am not sure if many others have noticed this stark difference, but it certainly bothered me.  3) Display : Granted, at this price, a display is impossible to be afforded to us, but it REALLY makes a big impact. You know, I think the WORST thing about the Shuffle is the lack of display. I just cannot see whats coming up next, and while this is great for some people, it just did not work for me.  4) Fast-forwarding/re-winding Tracks : This is impossible on Shuffle. Once you start a track you cannot go to your favorite part in it or anything. This makes it tedious, especially if like me, you have a 30 minute interview with Tori Amos on it, and you want to skip to minute 15. Shuffle makes sure that you sit through the WHOLE THING before you reach that point. This does not work for me. At all.  On the plus side, the price is low, the sound quality is good (though NOT as good as the Nano), and the small, compact feel of the Shuffle is great enough to make this a must-have.  Just keep in mind the four points above though. If even one of these points makes a difference to you, I would advise investing in either a Nano or a Video Ipod. They ARE better models, and with good reason.  Hope this helps! Vote Yes, if it did!  
<Overall>3

